East London - The Buffalo City Stadium in East is packed to capacity as tens of thousands of African National Congress supporters flocked to the venue for the ANC's 106 birthday celebrations on Saturday. City streets are crowded with many buses, minibus taxis, and other vehicles delivering ANC supporters to the stadium. Some came singing songs of unity, while others called for change and the removal of President Jacob Zuma. The event kicked off with entertainment and music.    
